500|$|Initially six {{reactors}} or [...] "piles" [...] were proposed, {{when the}} plutonium {{was to be}} used in <b>the</b> gun-type <b>Thin</b> <b>Man</b> bomb. In mid-1944 a simple gun-type bomb was found to be impractical for plutonium, and the more advanced Fat Man bomb required less plutonium. The number of piles was reduced to four and then three; and the number of chemical separation plants from four to three.|$|R
